<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Learning English</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="style-2.css"/>
    </head>

    <!--Please consider the opacity, which is what makes the colour in the Figma website different from this one.-->
    <!--Find a way using ID and classes to only change the container and not the text inside.-->

    <body>
        <div id="header-box">
            <p id="website-name">Learning English</p>
                
            <div id="nav-options">
                <p>Parts of speech</p>
                <p>Contact forms</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div id="content-box">
            <p class="title">Parts of Speech</p>

            <div id="description">
                <p class="parts-of-speech">Noun</p>
                <p>The name of a person, place, object or idea; the name is what something is referred as.</p>
                <p class="example"><b>Example:</b> My name is <b>Roger.</b> <br/> <b>Roger</b> is the name of the <b>person.</b></p>

                <hr style="width: 101%; border: 1px solid black;">

                <p class="parts-of-speech">Verb</p>
                <p>The action, state, or occurrence of a person, place object or idea; what happened, is or something someone did.</p>
                <p class="example"><b>Example:</b> Roger <b>flexed</b> his biceps<br/><b>Flexing</b> is the <b>action</b> Roger did.</p>

                <hr style="width: 101%; border: 1px solid black;">

                <p class="parts-of-speech">Adjective</p>
                <p>A word that describes a person, place object or idea; a word that specifies what something is.</p>
                <p class="example"><b>Example:</b> Roger is a <b>fast</b> runner.<br/><b>Fast describes</b> Roger as a runner.</p>

                <hr style="width: 101%; border: 1px solid black;">

                <p class="parts-of-speech">Adverb</p>
                <p>A word that describes the action, state or occurrence of a person, place or object; specifies the action of something</p>
                <p class="example"><b>Example:</b> Roger <b>slowly</b> lifts the box.<br/><b>Slowly describes</b> the <b>person's</b> action.</p>

                <p class="title">Punctuation</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>

body{
    background-color: #B8D7FF;
    font-family:'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
}

#header-box{
    border: 1px solid black;
    padding: 15px;
    background-color: #C9FFC7;
    border-radius: 15px;

    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
}

#website-name{
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 20px;
}

#nav-options{
    display: flex;
    gap: 30px;
}

#content-box{
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
}

#title{
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 30px;
    margin-top: 90px;
}

#description{
    
    border: 1px solid black;
    border-radius: 50px;
    padding: 60px;
    background-color: #52FFBA;
    width: 35%;
    height: 230px;
    text-align: center;
    
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;

}

#get-started{
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 23px;

    border: 1px solid black;
    border-radius: 50px;
    padding: 20px;
    background-color: #B8FFB5;
}